{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2d22b154-fbff-497f-845a-d36e7cead435","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform on .NET 8, the VSTest options move behind `--` using the new flag names:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage \\\n  --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Required package references** in your test project:\n\n| Extension | Package |\n|-----------|---------|\n| TRX report | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` |\n| Code coverage | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` |\n| Crash dump | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` |\n| Hang dump | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` |\n\n**Key differences:**\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura`\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m`\n- `--filter` syntax is preserved (VSTest-compatible filter expressions still work)\n\nAlso ensure your test project sets `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` in its `.csproj` so `dotnet test` delegates to the new platform.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a4878aee-6a29-46f4-ac51-c4cb8bf01dbf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter`  (same, but uses `--treenode-filter` for the new filter syntax, though `--filter` is still supported for compatibility)\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-coverage` with coverage settings (or uses Microsoft.CodeCoverage with `--coverage` and `--coverage-output-format cobertura`)\n\n\n- `--blame-crash` maps to `--crashdump`, while `--blame-hang` and its timeout option translate to `--hangdump` and `--hangdump-timeout` respectively\n\n, each requiring their corresponding extension packages.\n\nLooking at the Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents, the filter syntax remains compatible through the bridge layer, TRX reporting uses `--report-trx`, code coverage shifts to `--coverage` with format options, and the blame features get their own dedicated flags. When using `dotnet test` with this platform, arguments after `--` route to the test platform, though newer versions allow direct parameter passing. So with Microsoft.Testing.Platform on .NET 8, I need to either enable `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` in the project file to use `dotnet test` with arguments passed after `--`, or just run the test executable directly instead. I need to list out the required NuGet packages for this setup—the TRX reporting extension, code coverage tools, and the crash and hang dump extensions.","outputTokens":1572,"requestId":"BC3A:1CADF2:1B76656:1E89577:69FA9053"},"id":"25c0856d-09dd-438b-ab52-a0f36c32c983","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:50:53.613Z","parentId":"b605bd74-f9d1-4041-841a-1971ac997cc3"}
